metadata.label: description
metadata.value: Boy Scout Pack 1025 was sponsored by the First Baptist Church of College Park. Around 1962, the pack participated in an annual camping event in Croom, Maryland. From left to right are (first row) Boy Scout leader Harold Pits and Cub Scout den leader Harry Braxton Sr; (second row) Garnet Fields and Roy Fields; (third row) Harry Braxton Jr., Kenneth Brooks, unidentified, Samuel Howard, and Maseo Campbell Jr.; (fourth row) Dennis Harding, unidentified, Keith Webster, and Lester Brooks with the flag.

metadata.label: creator
metadata.value: Lakeland Community Heritage Project, Inc., Lakeland: African Americans in College Park (Charleston, SC: Arcadia Pub., 2009), 97.
